author: The Emporia Gazette
title: Three Spartan golfers advance to state
text:
Three Spartan golfers advance to state Council Grove wins seven-team Centre regional Three Spartan golfers advance to state The Emporia Gazette   0 comments 
The Emporia High girls golf team finished fourth at the regional meet in Leavenworth Monday, as three individuals will advance to state on Monday, Oct. 19. 
Senior Ashley DeBauge had the low score for EHS, with a combined 49 and 53 to total a 102 score, good for seventh overall and the best score for an individual placer. Sara Mitchell finished second for Emporia High with a 119 at Trails West Golf Course. The Spartan sophomore finished the course with a 60 on the front nine and shaved a stroke off when coming through the back. 
Kylia Floyd became the third Spartan and last individual to qualify, finishing her effort with a 60 and a 59 for a total score of 119. Hana Risley finished with a score of 131 while Makayla Kusmaul stroked a 134. 
Andover, Shawnee Heights and Seaman advanced to next week’s 5A state meet at Dubs Dread Golf Course in Kansas City, next Monday. 
CGHS wins seven-team Centre regional 
Council Grove’s golf team captured first at its regional meet, getting three top-10 finishes individually at the Herington Country Club. 
Jordan Carlson led her team with a third-place finish, posting a 96 that consisted of a 44 on the front and 52 on the back. Makenzie Downes shot 106 to finish fifth while Hailey Hower's 110 was good enough for ninth for Council Grove, which will take its entire team to the 3-2-1A state meet at Cherry Oaks Golf Course in Cheney. 
BrieAnna Grimmett posted a 114 for the Braves, who also got a 142 from Kylee Shaffer and 154 from Kirsten Bane. Council Grove's team score of 426 topped Silver Lake by 13 strokes, with St. Mary's finishing third at 441.
